The paper focuses on improving the efficiency and accuracy of neural networks for computer vision tasks, specifically object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the network, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on object detection datasets, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
